values:
So today I see a post that one of my friends neighbors baby stopped breathing, and was not doing well.&nbsp; At dinner a fried who works for the police dept mentions that a baby had died, and they had to investigate it.&nbsp; Get home, see facebook again and another friend posted wishing prayers and comfort for her neighbor and her neighbors brother and sister in law, who are also my friends.&nbsp; My brain of course puts all this together, and I send her a message to confrm.&nbsp; One of my really good friends lost his little boy today.&nbsp; he was a month and a half younger than Earl.&nbsp; this friend has had a rough time in the past.&nbsp; Made some bad decisions, and got into some things he shouldn&#39;t have.&nbsp; He had finally gotten everything together, finished college, met a girl, and had a baby he loved very very much.&nbsp; he recently got a promotion and is goign to be moving out of state soon.&nbsp; He&#39;s already working some there, but she and the baby have stayed here for now.&nbsp;&nbsp; They are getting married next month.

I can&#39;t even begin to imagine how bad this hurts them.&nbsp; I hope they are able to weather through it.&nbsp; I hope that I can help them in some way.&nbsp;&nbsp; I haven&#39;t been able to stop crying snce I heard.&nbsp; Luckily E is still to little to realize, and Weeji did a good job of keeping katie away from me.&nbsp;&nbsp;

Sometimes life just doesn&#39;t seem right.
